<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=375D88><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ueilunedakallabeth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eiluned Akallabeth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/21/02 2:33:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ftearsofveeshan25764frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=154.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Greetings, Tears..</span><hr size=1> Eiluned steps from the very shadows and casts a long look across the hall. Her pale eyes drift over the decor and then to the various faces gathered around, scrutinizing everything and everyone. She efforts a warm display, but nerves and nature only allow the elf a rather weak smile.<br>
<br>
&quot;Thanks for your hospitality, Moline. I think I shall have a glass of Neriak Nectar as I am rather parched after the long journey to your hall.&quot; She gathers the thick shadows that dress her and slips quietly over the stone floor, carefully navigating the furnishings appointed 'round the room.<br>
<br>
While many of her kind would move into a nice shadowed corner, Eiluned takes a spot near the blazing hearth. She basks in its glow, drinking in its warmth through her skin. Its for such comforts that her smile is fully realized. She shares it with the strange couple that greeted her arrival, Steoff and Eglath.<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh, I was sure I would meet you both!&quot; she says, her voice low and manner cool. The young necromancer gestures elegantly as she addresses the duo. &quot;You are both individuals of fame. Or, to be more accurate - notoriety. That you found each other is...interesting to say the least. I would think that your company keeps the guild quite lively. I can't wait to catch the gossip that's surely flying about.&quot;<br>
<br>
A servants approach steals Eiluned's attention for a moment; just long enough for her to take up a glass and thank the wench with a dismissive wave of her hand. She sips from her glass before speaking again. &quot;Ohh I think I'll be just fine here. Indeed...&quot; <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ueilunedakallabeth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eiluned Akallabeth</A> at: 10/21/02 2:57:06 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=375D88><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/uralstaan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ralstaan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/22/02 12:51:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ftearsofveeshan25764frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=154.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Greetings, Tears..</span><hr size=1> *catches her hand before she can take another sip*<br>
<br>
&quot;You will be fine when you have had a real drink to warm yourself with...not this honey-water.&quot;<br>
<br>
*motions for a tankard of ale from the serving girl*<br>
<br>
&quot;Here girl....take a swig of that before you go on.&quot;<br>
<br>
*folds his arms across his chest and awaits with a proud grin*<br>
<br>
