</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=375D88><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ueilunedakallabeth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eiluned Akallabeth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/22/02 5:33:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ftearsofveeshan25764frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=154.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Greetings, Tears..</span><hr size=1> Eiluned turns on Ralstaan with a look to be expected from one not accustomed to such &quot;handling&quot;. She raises a brow at the barbarian and casts a chilly look over her him. The smile at her lips seems oddly out of place.<br>
<br>
        &quot;My, aren't you boorish? I suppose it's just an aspect of your charm.&quot; humor lends a bit of warmth to her deep, indigo complexion. Her slender hand slips smoothly out of Ralstaan's grasp as she turns to eye the serving whench's load landing to the table top.<br>
<br>
        The young necromancer tries to obfuscate her disgust with a weak smile. &quot;You're so...thoughtful, Ralstaan. I'll have to come up with ways to 'thank' you for such a treat.&quot; Eiluned's voice carries lightly over nearby ears, that may or may not find its laced with just a hint of malice.<br>
<br>
        With a sigh, Eiluned takes up the heavy glass with both hands and lifts the drink to her lips. She winces, obviously not find the taste to her liking. The glass drops absently to the table, its contents spilling over the wood. She raises the shadowy sleeve of her robe to her lips to wipe the foul taste away. &quot;I'm not impressed by your tastes, Ralstaan..&quot;<br>
<br>
        That said the Teir'Dal gathers the skirt of her robe with one hand and makes her way over to a more tidy table. The sound of rustling silk moving over the stone floor scores her action. She pauses before taking her seat and darts a look back over her shoulder at Ralstaan. An easy grin targets the warrior. &quot;I fully expect you to make the matter good with an offering of the tavern's finest champagne.&quot;<br>
<br>
        With flourish she spins about, her skirts flying about her, and drops into the seat in a boneless motion. She settles in, legs elegantly crossed and elbow perched at the table's edge. She rests her head against her hand and grins. &quot;You're welcome to join me for a drink as I wait for the guild's officers to arrive.&quot; <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ueilunedakallabeth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eiluned Akallabeth</A> at: 10/22/02 5:35:31 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=375D88><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/btearsofveeshan25764.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eilunedakallabeth>Eiluned Akallabeth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/22/02 5:54:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ftearsofveeshan25764frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=154.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Greetings, Tears..</span><hr size=1> Eiluned's pale gaze pans over the room to spy the white wolf addressing her. She raises a brow at this, seeming very curious. &quot;There are none like you among my people, Salvia. None that change shape to such effect.<br>
<br>
&quot;My own limited experience has not delivered me into the company of one of Tunare's soldiers until now and I must say, I'm in awe.&quot; She stands from her seat and stalks over towards the druid. The necromancer takes her in with wide eyes and reaches out to pet Salvia's fur.<br>
<br>
&quot;It's so soft,&quot; she practically purrs. &quot;It reminds me of cloak I keep at the very back of my closet. Though that fur fails to compare to the coat that dresses you. I'm sure you'd fetch a lovely plat if...&quot; She stops herself, removes the hand and takes a step away from the wolf.<br>
<br>
Eiluned turns 'round to return to her seat. &quot;Well met, Salvia. It's good to know you, mistress. Your warm greeting is certainly appreciated. As for the barbarians..&quot; she turns to spy Ralstaan, her head cocked slightly to the side.<br>
<br>
&quot;My only interest in such creatures is in their prowess on the fields of battle. Their meaty skins make great shields and that is something to be appreciated&quot;<br>
<br>
That said, she lifts her glass in silent toast to Salvia and returns to her drinking and waiting. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=375D88><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/btearsofveeshan25764.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mirahze521>Mirahze521</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ToV Elder</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/22/02 10:57:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ftearsofveeshan25764frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=154.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Greetings, Tears..</span><hr size=1> &lt; Salvia eyes Eilund as she mutters the comment about her hide fetching plat.  Remembering the ways of other races she calms herself and smiles&gt;<br>
<br>
&quot;You are well met this day, despite the look you gave my hide.&quot; she says, letting a wolvish grin escape her lips.  There shall be a gathering of the guild early next week, if all goes smoothly.  I will get in touch with you about the details of it when the plans are more solid.  You are of course very welcome to attend.  It is most likely going to be a friendly gathering of folk teaching each other various languages and trades.&quot;<br>
<br>
&lt;Standing to her haunches, black tipped ears perk forward in a sign of friendship.&gt;<br>
<br>
&quot;I look forward to speaking with you more. But for now I must go.&quot;<br>
<br>
&lt;Salvia trots out the back door, where Ssolaria had beckoned her to og earlier.  A yelp echoes down the hallway and Salvia can be seen darting passed the messhall into the mainhall, water and soap flying from her fur.  Ssolaria is in hot pursuit, washbrush and bucket in hand&gt;   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=375D88><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/btearsofveeshan25764.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ralstaan>Ralstaan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/23/02 3:37:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ftearsofveeshan25764frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=154.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Greetings, Tears..</span><hr size=1> Ralstaan looks down at the tankard of ale and shakes his head before lifting it to his lips.  He drains what little was not spilled over the table and sets it down before making his way to the Necromancer.  As he pulls a stool out to have a seat next to her he motions for the serving girl to approach, and upon her arriving, he whispers something into her ear.  Though a slap across the rump would assure speedy service he remembers he is in the company of a woman of class and thinks better of it, though his eyes continue to follow his intended target as the serving girl saunters away.  After a fashion he turns to speak to Eilund.<br>
<br>
&quot;The finest champagne this tavern has to offer eh??  Well girl you have robbed me of my last bit of plat.....but there is no doubt in me that you are worth it and I should enjoy learning more of a fellow sister-in-arms....though from what I have already learned methinks you are more rogue than necromancer...&quot;<br>
<br>
He studies the look she offers him and attempts to identify it as either one of insult or flattery.  He remains studying her, chin resting on fist, when out of the corner of his eye he notices that two sparking glasses of champagne have been set out before them.  He watches her lift her glass to her lips and drink, and so as not to fall behind he lifts his as well, though with a hand much less practiced at it.  He gulps it without a taste.  As she sips the crystal clear champagne he smiles.  The look on her face this time is much easier to identify.<br>
<br>
&quot;Well girl I am happy that you accept my peace offering, and the next time I will save the ale for a stout barbarian lass.&quot;  He surpresses a chuckle as he notices her soft face twist at the memory of the aftertaste.  &quot;Now I hope you do not think a man boorish, but the hour grows late and I do not wish to keep you...there are elders for you to speak to.&quot;<br>
<br>
